# Flutter Developer Plugin - Cursor Rules

## Repository

This is `modulabs-io/flutter-developer-plugin`, a Claude Code plugin for Flutter development.

## Structure

```
agents/          # 21 specialized Flutter agents
skills/          # 33 slash command skills
commands/        # 3 feature scaffolding commands
hooks/           # Automated hooks configuration
.claude-plugin/  # Plugin manifest
```

## Agent Format

File: `agents/flutter-{domain}.md`

```markdown
---
name: flutter-{domain}
description: Brief description
allowed-tools: [Bash, Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Grep]
---

# Agent Title

## Core Responsibilities
## Patterns and Examples
## Decision Guidelines
```

## Skill Format

File: `skills/flutter-{action}/SKILL.md`

```markdown
# /flutter-{action}

## Usage
## Options
## Examples
## Instructions
## Agent Reference
```

## Naming

- Agents: `flutter-{domain}.md` (kebab-case)
- Skills: `flutter-{action}/SKILL.md`
- Commands: `flutter-{command}.md`

## Commits (Conventional)

```
type(scope): description
```

Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, chore
Scopes: agents, skills, commands, hooks, mcp, plugin

Examples:
- `feat(agents): add flutter-web-platform agent`
- `fix(skills): correct flutter-build steps`

## Code Style

- Use code blocks with language specifiers
- Provide practical examples
- Follow Flutter best practices

## Workflow

- Trunk-based development
- Direct commits to main or short-lived branches
- Pull latest before work
- Small, focused changes
